{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddc37536b-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1749d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1749d"},"text":"§ 1749d.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Cost of inspections and of providing representatives","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"On and after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-12-19"},"text":"December 19, 1963","children":[],"tail":", necessary expenses of inspections and of providing representatives at the site of projects being planned or undertaken by local public agencies pursuant to title I of the Housing Act of 1949, as amended ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1450"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 1450","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], projects financed through loans to educational institutions authorized by title IV of the Housing Act of 1950, as amended ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1749"},"text":"12 U.S.C. 1749","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], projects and facilities financed by loans to public agencies pursuant to title II of the Housing Amendments of 1955, as amended ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1491"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 1491","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], urban planning financed through grants to State and local government agencies pursuant to chapter 35 of title 40, and reserves of planned public works financed through advances to municipalities and other public agencies pursuant to chapter 35 of title 40, as amended, shall be compensated by such agencies or institutions by the payment of fixed fees which in the aggregate will cover the costs of rendering such services, and expenses for such purpose shall be considered nonadministrative; and for the purpose of providing such inspections, the Secretary of Housing and Urban Development may utilize any agency and such agency may accept reimbursement or payment for such services from such institutions, or the Secretary, and shall credit such amounts to the appropriations or funds against which such charges have been made."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddc37536c-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/215/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–215, title I","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 1963","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/77/437"},"text":"77 Stat. 437","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/174/s5"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–174, § 5","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1965-09-09"},"text":"Sept. 9, 1965","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/79/669"},"text":"79 Stat. 669","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddc37536d-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddc37536e-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddc37536f-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Housing Act of 1949, as amended, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-07-15/ch338"},"text":"act July 15, 1949, ch. 338","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/413"},"text":"63 Stat. 413","children":[],"tail":". Title I of the Housing Act of 1949 which was classified generally to subchapter II (§ 1450 et seq.) of chapter 8A of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare, was omitted from the Code pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s5316"},"text":"section 5316 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" which terminated the authority to make grants or loans under such chapter after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1975","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1441"},"text":"section 1441 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Housing Act of 1950, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-04-20/ch94"},"text":"act Apr. 20, 1950, ch. 94","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/48"},"text":"64 Stat. 48","children":[],"tail":". Title IV of the Act was classified generally to this subchapter and was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/498/tVII/s702"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–498, title VII, § 702","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/1545"},"text":"100 Stat. 1545","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title of 1950 Amendment note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1701"},"text":"section 1701 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Housing Amendments of 1955, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1955-08-11/ch783"},"text":"act Aug. 11, 1955, ch. 783","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/69/645"},"text":"69 Stat. 645","children":[],"tail":". Title II of the Act was classified generally to chapter 8B (§ 1491 et seq.) of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare, and was omitted from the Code pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s5316"},"text":"section 5316 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" which terminated authority to make grants or loans under such title II after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1975","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1701"},"text":"section 1701 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"iddc375370-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“Chapter 35 of title 40” substituted in text for “title VII of the Housing Act of 1954, as amended” and for “title VII of the Housing Act of 1954” on authority of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/217/s5/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–217, § 5(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1303"},"text":"116 Stat. 1303","children":[],"tail":", the first section of which enacted Title 40, Public Buildings, Property, and Works."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Independent Offices Appropriation Act, 1964, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/215"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–215","children":[],"tail":", and not as part of the National Housing Act which comprises this chapter or title IV of the Housing Act of 1950 which comprised this subchapter. Similar provisions were contained in the following prior appropriation acts:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-03"},"text":"Oct. 3, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/741/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–